tags.description:
In order to receive less messages from a given trigger, you can set a subscription filter.

The filter must be a valid [JSON Schema](https://json-schema.org/learn/getting-started-step-by-step.html) object (or JSON-stringified object).

A subscription with a filter will test it against every message that is triggered. Only events that match the filters will be delivered to the subscription endpoint.

### Quickstart

You can easily filter webhooks based on the message `metadata`. See below for a couple of common use examples.

Given the following webhook message:

```json
{
  "service": "delivery",
  "entity": "shipping",
  "eventName": "scheduled",
  "metadata": {
    "id": "634eb9fc96cdaa068d8cf42a",
    "status": "scheduled",
    "displayId": "290922-AHHS10",
    "refId": "2RT-90922",
    "trackingId": "UHES873NSDA8-01",
    "realTimeId": "211004-BDZ82NH1",
    "integ": "uber",
    "type": "express_delivery",
    "shippingTypeId": "633c8e225d10601e4aed2b9d",
    "shippingTypeTitle": "Standard delivery",
    "carrierId": "633c8e5f1ee1d732b1158bc9",
    "carrierName": "Standard delivery Uber",
    "companyId": "633c8e80a4915c4ea17ccaca",
    "companyName": "Uber Express",
    "price": 10
  },
  "eventDate": "2021-02-23T21:53:57.938Z"
}
```

#### Filter by a property value

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "integ": {
      "const": "uber"
    }
  },
  "required": ["integ"]
}
```

#### Filter by a property multiple valid values

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "type": {
      "enum": ["express_delivery", "delivery"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["type"]
}
```

#### Filter by an optional numeric minimum value (for example, for filtering non-free shippings)

> Not including the `price` in the `required` array will also match events where the `price` is not set

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "price": {
      "exclusiveMinimum": 0
    }
  }
}
```

#### Filter by a property, excluding one or more values

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["sellerSalesChannelReferenceId"],
  "if": {
    "properties": {
      "sellerSalesChannelReferenceId": {
        "const": "sales-channel-to-ignore" # Replace this with your own sales channel
        # or for multiple values use "enum": ["sales-channel-to-ignore-1", "sales-channel-to-ignore-2"]
      }
    }
  },
  "then": {
    "properties": {
      "sellerSalesChannelReferenceId": {
        "type": "string",
        "const": "no"
      }
    }
  },
  "else": {
    "properties": {
      "sellerSalesChannelReferenceId": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
